     <body>
     <div type="afterword">
   <head>Lenuoy of .R. Copland</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>O lytle quayre, god gyue the wel to sayle</l>
      <l>To that good sheppe, ycleped Bertelet</l>
      <l>For through it thou mayst the more preuayle</l>
      <l>Agaynst the rockes, that blyndly ben yset</l>
      <l>Up on the land thy substaunce for to fret</l>
      <l>And from all nacyous, if that it be thy lot</l>
      <l>Lest thou be hurt, medle not with a Scot.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>¶And to thy readers, as custome is to say</l>
      <l>Do thy deuoyr, but to wydowes chefely</l>
      <l>Desyringe them to take it as in play</l>
      <l>For that to do, was myne entent truely</l>
      <l>Desyryng them to accept my fantasy</l>
      <l>And to amende thyne englyshe where is nede</l>
      <l>For to pastime myne intent was in dede.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
